data.chText: 规格；规范；明细单；说明书
data.enText: a detailed description of how sth is, or should be, designed or made
the technical specifications of the new model (= of car)

data.chText: 房子完全是按照我们的工程设计书建造的。
data.enText: The house has been built exactly to our specifications .

data.chText: 办公室是按高规格装潢的。
data.enText: The office was furnished to a high specification .

simple_means.memory_skill: spec 外观；种类 + ification …化 → 具体说明

tr: a restriction that is insisted upon as a condition for an agreement
(patent law) a document drawn up by the applicant for a patent of invention that provides an explicit and detailed description of the nature and use of an invention
a detailed description of design criteria for a piece of work

value.def: A specification is a requirement which is clearly stated, for example about the necessary features in the design of something.

example.ex: Troll's exclusive, personalized luggage is made to our own exacting specifications in heavy-duty PVC/nylon...
example.tran: 特罗尔专用的、个性化的行李箱是按照我们自己严格的规格要求用耐用聚氯乙烯/尼龙材料定制的。

example.ex: Legislation will require UK petrol companies to meet an EU specification for petrol.
example.tran: 法规将要求英国的汽油公司必须达到欧盟对汽油的规格要求。
受到严格的岗位要求限制的官员们

rootsaffixes.indicate: = look, kind, sort 外观；种类
rootsaffixes.title: spec(i)

partsOfSpeech.dec: con 共同 + spec 外观；种类 + ific 使…的 → 同种的
spec 外观；种类 + ial …的 →〔属于〕某种类 → 特别的
special 特别的；专门的 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 特点；特产
special 特别的；专门的 + ize …化 → 专门化；专攻
speci 外观；种类 + es → 种类，物种
spec 外观；种类 + ific 产生…的 → 分门别类的 → 具体的
spec 外观；种类 + ification …化 → 具体说明
speci 外观；种类 + men 表实物名词 → 作为某一种类的样品 → 标本
speci 外观；种类 + ous …的 → 外观相似，而实质不是 → 似是而非的
